parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the service brakes, hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal burning odor coming from the engine compartment
vehicle caught on fire underneath the hood
oil gauge indicating hot oil
grayish colored smoke coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can cause a delay in fixing the issue, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Notification of NHTSA Campaign Number: 22V051000 (Service Brakes
Hydraulic) received
but the part to do the recall repair was unavailable
exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and seizure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause fires.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking or clunking sound
the vehicle loses power
the oil light flashes
the vehicle stalls or shuts down
smoke or fire comes from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical harness can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or catch fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Delays and Lack of Transparency
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs and lack of transparency from the manufacturer and dealerships can put vehicle owners at risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to unresolved safety issues.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notices but are unable to get repairs done
dealerships lack parts or provide inadequate information
manufacturers fail to provide timely solutions or assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.

or windows break.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and stalling can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle loses power while driving at high speeds.

the vehicle loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address airbag and fuel line recalls can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the risk of airbag deployment or fuel leaks.
